  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your innate magic comes from draconic magic that was mingled with your blood or that of your ancestors. Most often, sorcerers with this origin trace their descent back to a mighty sorcerer of ancient times who made a bargain with a dragon or who might even have claimed a dragon parent. Some of these bloodlines are well established in the world, but most are obscure. Any given sorcerer could be the first of a new bloodline, as a result of a pact or some other exceptional circumstance.</p>\n<h3>Draconic Bloodline Features</h3>\n<p>1st Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.mdpqLMIMdI6Nt9CD]{Dragon Ancestor}, @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.rH7ARaiocr7T58Do]{Draconic Resilience}</p>\n<p>6th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.HTmNwDYLX1a4JhXB]{Elemental Affinity}</p>\n<p>14th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.x5GMOufjrgodgchS]{Dragon Wings}</p>\n<p>18th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.4JCv2VA1CY0j5Dvv]{Draconic Presence}</p>",
